body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, welcome to Luxury Motors. My name is Noah Wilson. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great to meet you, Janice. Could you please provide me with your phone number, one zero zero three four five two zero zero nine eight?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Janice. And may I also have your email address, jflores@example.com?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for sharing that information, Janice. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, I just wanted to inquire about the product quality. I'm relieved to know it's top-notch.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I'm glad to hear that, Janice. Thank you for reaching out to us. We appreciate your feedback. Have a wonderful day!
